Off-Campus students seek says option; Vote probably
By MOLLY MCGUIRE
l Off-campus seniors may be
able to forest their board fees
this year, thus giving up their
"privilege" to eat SAGA food
in the dining calls, If an allItudent references proposed
Tuesday by the Student Affairs
Committee (SAC) indicates support for the measure.
The references will determine
it the majority of the student
body is willing to pay a flight
increase in board fees that
would enable their offrcampus
peers to say goodbye to SAGA
and find for themselvesi
The recent action by the SAC
is only the latest in a series of
measures taken to explore the
possibilities of giving students
options to the present policy of
mandatory board fees. At the
present time, all students must
pay for board except married
students and those originally
mm the city of Grinnell.
Last spring, alter complaints
by future off-campus seniors
and in light of the response to
the SAGA committee’s questionnaire (where students indicated a desire to be able to
forest the blanket board fee),
the SAC issued a list of suggestions to the administration,
asking them to find specific information about various possible options. About a month
later, on May la, the committee issued a recommendation
to President suggest for a temporary plan for the tall games—
her: they asked that “students
not in college housing be given
the option of not paying the
board fee, and thus not eating
in the campus dining hall."
this proposal was for the loss—
70 school year only, until a
more satisfactory plan could be
worked out, The committee
managed that there “may be
some problems in the implementation of the recommendation. ”
Problems there were. Because of the late date of the
suggestion and the illness of
one of the key personnel involved, nothing was done about
answering nr improving the
proposal until this 1811. Meanwhile, about seven offrcampus
seniors decided to refuse to pay
their board fees at registration,
hoping to put pressure on the
administration to do something
immediately about the recommendation. After being sent to
talk to six different adminisr
station officials, the students
were given an estimated to
pay their board fees by Mona ,
day, Sept 8th, or they would
not be considered students at
the college. (All have paid;
students they still are.) They
were also told that the means
were currently considering the
recommendation.
Considering it they were. On
September 5, following official
procedure, President suggest
sent Professor Edgar collins,
chairman of the SAC, a response to the suggestion of last
spring. in it he stated that he
saw problems in the implementation of the request, and that
he had asked the means to take
certain measures to “begin the
necessary analyses that would
provide us with descriptions of
liable options for long- range
food service arrangements for
all students. ”
suggest cited the possibility
of a rise in board charges next
semester and thereafter for
those focused to make up for
those executed from paying
board (the fewer students paying, the higher the individual
board cost will be), and the
possible need of a checking
system In the dining calls, He
felt that because of these possibilities, every student should
be informed and be able to
have a say in the issue.
 
